<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the synthetic demo group
    `x_casemgmt_demo_team`. This is the SOLE XML file in the
    `servicenow-case-management-poc/seed-data/groups/` directory per the
    AAP Section 0.4.1 explicit directory layout, and is the canonical
    target for every demo case's `assigned_group` reference.

    Group purpose (per AAP Section 0.5.6 ACL Matrix and Validation Gate 3):
      The "Assigned only" rule for the case_agent role is defined as
      "cases where assigned_agent = current user OR assigned_group
      contains current user". Without a demo group whose membership
      includes the demo agent, the second clause of that rule cannot be
      exercised by an operator during Validation Gate 3 (ACLs). This
      group exists exclusively to satisfy that validation requirement on
      the cases where the demo agent is reachable via group membership
      rather than direct assignment.

    Single-member rule (per agent prompt key insight #2 and #6):
      ONLY the demo agent (x_casemgmt_demo_agent) is added as a member of
      this group at runtime. The demo manager (x_casemgmt_demo_manager)
      and demo viewer (x_casemgmt_demo_viewer) are explicitly NOT members.
        - The manager has Read All / Write All / Create / Delete privileges
          via the case_manager role's table-level ACLs, so group membership
          is irrelevant for that persona.
        - The viewer has Read All across all three custom tables via the
          case_viewer role's READ ACLs, so group membership is irrelevant
          for that persona as well.
        - Adding either of them as group members would be harmless from
          a privilege standpoint but misleading for documentation and
          test scenarios; the single-member rule keeps the demo data
          unambiguous.

    The membership row is NOT serialized in this file. Per AAP Section
    0.4.1's directory layout and the agent prompt key insight #6, the
    `groups/` folder contains exactly ONE XML file (this one). The
    `sys_user_grmember` row that adds the demo agent as a member of this
    group is created at runtime by the idempotent server-side seed
    script at `../../scripts/seed_demo_data.js` via the helper
    `ensureGroupMembership(DEMO.USERS.AGENT, DEMO.GROUP)`. This is a
    deliberate, AAP-aligned design choice; do NOT add a separate XML
    file for the membership row.

    Why this group record lives in the SCOPED Update Set even though
    `sys_user_group` is a global OOB table (per the agent prompt and AAP
    Section 0.7.2 scope-namespace exclusivity):
      The scoped Update Set's deliverable is fully self-contained: the
      reviewer must be able to install the Update Set on a fresh PDI and
      immediately exercise all seven validation gates. The demo group
      is required by Gate 3 (ACL role-based access) — specifically the
      "case_agent cannot access unassigned cases" pass row. Tracking the
      demo group inside the scoped Update Set ensures it imports together
      with the rest of the application; the scope binding via <sys_scope>
      and <sys_package> source attribute groups it with the scoped app
      even though its parent table (sys_user_group) is global. No
      global-scope WRITES are performed: only an INSERT into sys_user_group
      (a data table) — the OOB sys_user_group dictionary, ACLs, and form
      layouts are never modified.

    Authoring rules honored (per AAP Sections 0.7.1 / 0.7.2 and the
    agent prompt's eight authoring rules):

      Rule 1 — Synthetic Only:
        name        = "x_casemgmt_demo_team" (clearly synthetic with the
                      `_demo_` infix; unmistakably non-real)
        description = "Demo team for the case-management POC. Synthetic
                      group; no production members." (literal fixed
                      synthetic text containing the tripwire keyword
                      `Synthetic`; per agent prompt key insight #10)
        NO real LDAP/AD groups, NO real production team names (no
        Engineering, HR, Sales, Operations, etc.), NO real production
        members.

      Rule 2 — Zero Hardcoded sys_id Cross-References:
        The group's OWN <sys_id> below is the record's primary key,
        which is acceptable per AAP rule (it is NOT a reference to
        any other record). It is a deterministic 32-character lowercase
        hex value (MD5 of the canonical group name "x_casemgmt_demo_team"
        => f5457651a57f6fadb32d3a09f963855b) so the Update Set engine
        resolves the same sys_id on every PDI import, making the case
        `assigned_group` cross-references and the seed script's
        lookupGroupSysId() helper idempotent.
        The <sys_scope> and <sys_package> reference fields resolve by
        display_value/source attributes against the scoped application's
        sys_scope record — NOT by hardcoded sys_id literals.
        NO <manager>, <parent>, <cost_center> reference fields are
        populated, so no other reference-resolution concerns arise.

      Rule 3 — Scope Binding:
        <sys_scope> binds this group record to the scoped application
        whose sys_scope.source is `x_casemgmt` (defined in
        ../../app/sys_scope/x_casemgmt.xml). The display_value attribute
        is "Case Management". The <sys_package> follows the same pattern
        with the source attribute pointing at the scope source name.
        This matches the convention used by every other scoped artifact
        in the Update Set (users, roles, ACLs, dictionary entries,
        choices, etc.).
        Although `sys_user_group` is a global OOB table, the SCOPED demo
        group is tracked in the scoped Update Set so the deliverable is
        fully self-contained per the folder requirements: "the SCOPED
        demo group is tracked in the scoped Update Set for full
        deliverable encapsulation."

      Rule 4 — No Production Data:
        No real LDAP/AD groups, no real production team names, no real
        production members, no realistic email addresses, no realistic
        identifiers. The synthetic placeholder values (the literal
        `x_casemgmt_demo_team` name and the description text containing
        `Synthetic`) are unmistakably non-real.

      Rule 5 — Idempotency Anchor:
        The group's idempotent key is <name> = "x_casemgmt_demo_team".
        The companion seed script ../../scripts/seed_demo_data.js
        ensureGroup() helper queries sys_user_group by name BEFORE
        inserting; the action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE" attribute on the inner
        <sys_user_group> element ensures the same behavior at Update Set
        import time. This <name> value MUST EXACTLY match every
        downstream reference: the seed script's DEMO.GROUP constant,
        the `assigned_group` field on cases 02 through 10 under
        ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_*.xml, the membership row created
        by the seed script (ensureGroupMembership), and any ACL
        conditions or validation subflows that resolve groups by name.

      Rule 6 — Single Member Rule:
        Only the demo agent is a member of this group. The membership
        row is created at runtime by the seed script's
        ensureGroupMembership(DEMO.USERS.AGENT, DEMO.GROUP) helper, NOT
        by an XML file in this folder. This XML file does not encode
        that membership; it only declares the group itself.

      Rule 7 — Minimum Field Set:
        ONLY the minimum content fields required by the agent prompt are
        populated: active, description, name. All additional
        sys_user_group columns (manager, parent, email, cost_center,
        roles, source, type, hourly_rate, default_assignee, vendors,
        u_*) are auto-defaulted by the platform on first import. This
        keeps the file small, avoids dependencies on other global tables
        (cmn_cost_center, sys_user, sys_user_group parent), and makes
        the record resilient to ServiceNow release-version drift across
        Yokohama / Zurich / Australia.

      Rule 8 — Scoped Update Set XML conventions:
        Root element: <record_update table="sys_user_group">
        Inner element: <sys_user_group action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"> for
        idempotent re-import per AAP Section 0.7.1 round-trip-
        verification.
        UTF-8 encoding declared in XML prolog.
        Boolean values lowercase: <active>true</active>.
        Element ordering: alphabetical (matching the user records, role
        records, and every other XML in the scoped Update Set).

    Cross-dependencies (per AAP Section 0.5.2):

      This group IS REFERENCED BY (these files resolve THIS group by
      <name> = "x_casemgmt_demo_team", NOT by sys_id literal):
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_02.xml  (Open, General Inquiry)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_03.xml  (In Progress, General Inquiry)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_04.xml  (Pending, General Inquiry)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_05.xml  (Resolved, General Inquiry)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_06.xml  (Closed, General Inquiry)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_07.xml  (Open, Complaint)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_08.xml  (In Progress, Complaint)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_09.xml  (Resolved, Complaint)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_10.xml  (Closed, Complaint)
            (cases 02-10 use this group as their `assigned_group`
            reference; case 01 (Draft, General Inquiry) is pre-assignment
            and does NOT reference this group)
        - ../../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml
            (Draft -> Open transition requires assigned_group populated)
        - ../../flows/sub_flows/validate_inprogress_transition.xml
            (Open -> In Progress requires assigned_agent is a member of
            assigned_group; the membership row enables this validation
            to pass on cases 03-06 and 08-10)
        - ../../business_rules/x_casemgmt_validate_assigned_agent_membership.xml
            (same group-membership validation, before-update layer)
        - ../../acl/x_casemgmt_case_read_agent_assigned.xml
        - ../../acl/x_casemgmt_case_write_agent_assigned.xml
            ("Assigned only" ACL second clause:
             gs.getUser().isMemberOf(current.assigned_group.toString());
             the demo agent's membership in this group enables that
             clause to grant access)
        - ../../scripts/seed_demo_data.js
            (DEMO.GROUP constant equals this group name; the script's
            lookupGroupSysId(groupName) helper resolves this group's
            sys_id by name lookup; the ensureGroupMembership helper
            creates the demo agent's membership row at runtime)

      This group IS NOT referenced by:
        - case 01 (Draft, General Inquiry) — pre-assignment, no
          assigned_group set on this case
        - any task's reference field (tasks reference users by
          assigned_to, not groups)
        - any party's reference field (parties reference users via
          person reference or companies via organization reference, not
          groups)

      Update Set ordering (per AAP Section 0.5.2):
        - This record MUST be loaded AFTER the scope/app records under
          ../../app/ (since <sys_scope>/<sys_package> reference the
          scope's source).
        - This record MUST be loaded AFTER the demo user records under
          ../users/ (although the membership row is not serialized in
          this folder, the loading order keeps the seed-data segment
          internally consistent and ensures the seed-script
          ensureGroupMembership helper has both endpoints resolvable
          when it runs post-import).
        - This record MUST be loaded BEFORE:
            * the role assignments under ../role_assignments/ (these are
              unrelated dependencies but the loading order keeps the
              seed-data segment internally consistent per the folder
              requirements)
            * any case under ../cases/ (cases 02-10 reference this group
              via `assigned_group` resolved by name lookup; this group
              must exist before those cases deserialize)

    Source-side semantic reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported)
    per AAP Section 0.8.1:
      - acm-services/acm-service-users/src/main/java/com/armedia/acm/
        services/users/model/ApplicationRolesConfig.java
        Holds `application.roles` as a List<String> bound from external
        configuration via @ListValue("application.roles"); exposes
        `MERGE_APPLICATION_ROLES_OP = "application.~roles"`. Semantic
        anchor only: ArkCase's role/group configuration model (which
        would be backed by LDAP/AD groups in production) is replaced in
        the target by named scoped roles plus a single fully synthetic
        in-platform group. ArkCase's broader user/group infrastructure
        is NOT replicated; the ServiceNow target uses one synthetic
        in-platform group on the OOB sys_user_group table with
        deliberately minimal field set.
      - ArkCase's underlying group mechanism (LDAP/AD-backed groups in
        production) is NOT replicated; the ServiceNow target uses fully
        synthetic in-platform groups on the OOB sys_user_group table.

    Validation hooks (per the agent prompt):
      - The XML well-formedness check (xmllint with no-output flag)
        returns zero errors.
      - No-PII grep returns zero matches against (production|engineer|
        hr |sales|operations|@gmail|@yahoo|@outlook|@hotmail|\.com|\.org|
        \.net) — synthetic name and description only.
      - No-extra-fields grep returns zero matches against (manager|
        parent|email|cost_center|roles|source|u_) (excluding
        sys_class_name, sys_created_by, sys_id, sys_package, sys_scope,
        sys_update_name which are sys_* housekeeping fields).
      - The <name> value matches downstream references exactly across
        all 9 case demo XMLs and the seed script's DEMO.GROUP constant.
      - The concrete scope identifier `casemgmt` appears in the name,
        sys_update_name, sys_package source, and file path — NOT
        pre-substituted with a concrete scope id (per agent prompt key
        insight #1).
-->
<record_update table="sys_user_group">
    <sys_user_group action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <description>Demo team for the case-management POC. Synthetic group; no production members.</description>
        <name>x_casemgmt_demo_team</name>
        <sys_class_name>sys_user_group</sys_class_name>
        <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by>
        <sys_id>f5457651a57f6fadb32d3a09f963855b</sys_id>
        <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_casemgmt">x_casemgmt</sys_package>
        <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_casemgmt</sys_scope>
        <sys_update_name>sys_user_group_x_casemgmt_demo_team</sys_update_name>
    </sys_user_group>
</record_update>
